== Events == * [[Emperor Tenji]] 8th year（[[Julian calendar]] [[669]] [[November 13]]） – On his deathbed, [[藤原鎌足|Nakatomi Kamatari]] was bestowed the surname [[藤原氏|Fujiwara]] by Emperor Tenji. * [[Tenpyō]] 15th year ([[Julian calendar]] [[743]] [[November 5]]） – Emperor Shōmu issued an edict for the construction of the Great Buddha at Tōdai-ji. * [[:en:Hōen|Hoen]] 6th year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1140|1140]] [[November 26]]） – Sato Yoshikiyo, a northern retainer of former Emperor Toba, took the tonsure and began calling himself Saigyō. * [[:en:Reiwa era|Reiwa]] 4th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[2022]] [[November 8]]） – A total lunar eclipse and an eclipse of Uranus were observed simultaneously.
== Births == * [[:en:Kaei|Kaei]] 5th year（[[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1852|1852]] [[November 26]]） – Yamamoto Gonnohyōe, the 16th and 22nd Prime Minister of Japan and an Admiral (d. [[1933]]). * [[:en:Keiō|Keiō]] 2nd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1866|1866]] [[November 21]]） – The first Konishiki Hachijukichi, the 17th Yokozuna (d. [[1914]]). * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 5th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1872|1872]] [[November 15]]） – Okamoto Kido, a novelist (d. [[1939]]).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] 1st year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1573|1573]] [[November 9]]） – Shimazu Katsuhisa, the 14th head of the Shimazu Clan (born [[:en:1503|1503]]).
