{{Not to be confused with|October 15|qq=October 15}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=十月十五|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 10월 15일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar October|qq=}} '''October 15''' is the 15th day of the month {{ill|October (Lunisolar)|ja|October (Old Calendar)|1=Kannazuki|2=ja|3=10月 (旧暦)|lt=October (Kannazuki)|1=Kannazuki|2=ja|3=10月 (旧暦)|1=Kannazuki|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/October (Lunisolar)|13=User:Immanuelle/Kannazuki|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}}, the 10th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|Old Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|Rokuyō|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} day is {{ill|Shakkō|ja|Shakkō|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shakkō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.
== Events == * [[Emperor Tenji]] 8th year（[[Julian calendar]] [[:en:669|669]] [[November 13]]） – On his deathbed, [[藤原鎌足|Nakatomi Kamatari]] was bestowed the surname [[藤原氏|Fujiwara]] by Emperor Tenji. * [[Tenpyō]] 15th year ([[Julian calendar]] [[743]] [[November 5]]） – Emperor Shōmu issued an edict for the construction of the Great Buddha at Tōdai-ji. * [[:en:Hōen|Hoen]] 6th year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1140|1140]] [[November 26]]） – Sato Yoshikiyo, a northern retainer of former Emperor Toba, took the tonsure and began calling himself Saigyō. * [[:en:Reiwa era|Reiwa]] 4th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:2022|2022]] [[November 8]]） – A total lunar eclipse and an eclipse of Uranus were observed simultaneously.
== Births == * [[:en:Kaei|Kaei]] 5th year（[[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1852|1852]] [[November 26]]） – Yamamoto Gonnohyōe, the 16th and 22nd Prime Minister of Japan and an Admiral (d. [[:en:1933|1933]]). * [[:en:Keiō|Keiō]] 2nd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1866|1866]] [[November 21]]） – The first Konishiki Hachijukichi, the 17th Yokozuna (d. [[:en:1914|1914]]). * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 5th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1872|1872]] [[November 15]]） – Okamoto Kido, a novelist (d. [[:en:1939|1939]]).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] 1st year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1573|1573]] [[November 9]]） – Shimazu Katsuhisa, the 14th head of the Shimazu Clan (born [[:en:1503|1503]]).
