'''October 15''' is the 15th day of the month {{ill|October (Lunisolar)|ja|October (Old Calendar)|1=Kannazuki|2=ja|3=10月 (旧暦)|lt=October (Kannazuki)|1=Kannazuki|2=ja|3=10月 (旧暦)|1=Kannazuki|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/October (Lunisolar)|13=User:Immanuelle/Kannazuki|comment=enwiki is a redirect}}, the 10th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|Old Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|Rokuyō|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} day is {{ill|Shakkō|ja|Shakkō|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shakkō|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.

== Events ==
* {{ill|Emperor Tenji|en|Emperor Tenji|WD=Q314802|lt=Emperor Tenji|1=Emperor Tenji}} 8th year（{{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|669|en|669|WD=Q31115|lt=669|1=669}} {{ill|November 13|en|November 13|WD=Q2984|lt=November 13|1=November 13}}） – On his deathbed, [[藤原鎌足|Nakatomi Kamatari]] was bestowed the surname [[藤原氏|Fujiwara]] by Emperor Tenji.
* {{ill|Tenpyō|en|Tenpyō|WD=Q1199879|lt=Tenpyō|1=Tenpyō}} 15th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|743|en|743|WD=Q23604|lt=743|1=743}} {{ill|November 5|en|November 5|WD=Q2993|lt=November 5|1=November 5}}） – Emperor Shōmu issued an edict for the construction of the Great Buddha at Tōdai-ji.
* {{ill|Hōen|en|Hōen|WD=Q1193929|lt=Hoen|1=Hōen}} 6th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1140|en|1140|WD=Q19611|lt=1140|1=1140}} {{ill|November 26|en|November 26|WD=Q3019|lt=November 26|1=November 26}}） – Sato Yoshikiyo, a northern retainer of former Emperor Toba, took the tonsure and began calling himself Saigyō.
* {{ill|Reiwa era|en|Reiwa era|WD=Q62609017|lt=Reiwa|1=Reiwa era}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|2022|en|2022|WD=Q49625|lt=2022|1=2022}} {{ill|November 8|en|November 8|WD=Q2990|lt=November 8|1=November 8}}） – A total lunar eclipse and an eclipse of Uranus were observed simultaneously.

== Births ==
* {{ill|Kaei|en|Kaei|WD=Q1146125|lt=Kaei|1=Kaei}} 5th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1852|en|1852|WD=Q7661|lt=1852|1=1852}} {{ill|November 26|en|November 26|WD=Q3019|lt=November 26|1=November 26}}） – Yamamoto Gonnohyōe, the 16th and 22nd Prime Minister of Japan and an Admiral (d. {{ill|1933|en|1933|WD=Q18726|lt=1933|1=1933}}).
* {{ill|Keiō|en|Keiō|WD=Q776775|lt=Keiō|1=Keiō}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1866|en|1866|WD=Q7712|lt=1866|1=1866}} {{ill|November 21|en|November 21|WD=Q3023|lt=November 21|1=November 21}}） – The first Konishiki Hachijukichi, the 17th Yokozuna (d. {{ill|1914|en|1914|WD=Q2083|lt=1914|1=1914}}).
* {{ill|Meiji era|en|Meiji era|WD=Q3125096|lt=Meiji|1=Meiji era}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1872|en|1872|WD=Q7753|lt=1872|1=1872}} {{ill|November 15|en|November 15|WD=Q2982|lt=November 15|1=November 15}}） – Okamoto Kido, a novelist (d. {{ill|1939|en|1939|WD=Q18639|lt=1939|1=1939}}).

== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Tenshō (Momoyama period)|en|Tenshō (Momoyama period)|WD=Q1145058|lt=Tenshō Era|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1573|en|1573|WD=Q6678|lt=1573|1=1573}} {{ill|November 9|en|November 9|WD=Q2991|lt=November 9|1=November 9}}） – Shimazu Katsuhisa, the 14th head of the Shimazu Clan (born {{ill|1503|en|1503|WD=Q6141|lt=1503|1=1503}}).

